# Facebook WinForms Desktop App (.NET 4 / C#)

This project is a Windows desktop application built using **C# and .NET Framework 4**, developed as a final academic project.  
It integrates with the **Facebook Graph API** to fetch, display, and analyze user data in a clean, desktop environment.

---

## ðŸ“Œ Features

- Facebook login via OAuth
- View and interact with personal feed and posts
- **Stat Center**: A dedicated tab for analyzing top-liked posts, top-engaged users, and more
- Modular architecture following **OOP** and **design patterns** (e.g., Singleton, Strategy)
- Built using **WinForms**, with an emphasis on clean UI and maintainable backend

---

## ðŸ›  Tech Stack

- C# / .NET Framework 4
- WinForms (Desktop UI)
- Facebook Graph API
- JSON.NET
- Git & Visual Studio


## ðŸš€ Getting Started

1. Clone the repository  
   `git clone https://github.com/ofekcofman98/facebook-winforms-app.git`

2. Open the solution in **Visual Studio**

3. Set up a **Facebook Developer App**  
   - Get your App ID and App Secret  
   - Configure OAuth Redirect URI  
   - Insert credentials into the app configuration

4. Run the project!

* NOTE: you need to be in Administrators/developers/testers list for running the project. Pls make contact me to get permissions
